import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['delay'].hist(bins=50)
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['delay'] = pd.to_numeric(data['delay'], errors='coerce')
    data['distance'] = pd.to_numeric(data['distance'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['delay', 'distance'])
    plt.scatter(data['distance'], data['delay'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Distance (miles)')
    plt.ylabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between flight distance and delay time?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['time'], format='%H:%M:%S', errors='ignore')
    plt.hist(data['time'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Flight Duration')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight durations?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
